## 1. File Integrity
- [ ] All files present and named per delivery convention: `[client]-[deliverable]-[version]-[date].[ext]`
- [ ] File sizes within expected range (flag if >2x expected)
- [ ] No embedded fonts causing reflow on recipient systems
- [ ] Source files included per agreement (Figma link, .psd, .ai, etc.)

## 2. Brand Compliance
- [ ] Logo variant correct for background (dark/light/reversed)
- [ ] Logo minimum size respected
- [ ] Logo clear space present
- [ ] Brand colors only (spot-check 3 samples against palette)
- [ ] Approved typefaces only — no system-font substitutions
- [ ] No unlicensed stock imagery

## 3. Copy & Content
- [ ] All copy proofread (spelling, grammar, punctuation)
- [ ] All placeholder text removed ("Lorem ipsum", "TBD", "REPLACE ME")
- [ ] Legal lines present where required (©, ™, disclaimers)
- [ ] URLs and email addresses are live and correct
- [ ] Version numbers / dates are current

## 4. Technical Specifications
{% if "web" in platform_targets | lower %}
- [ ] Images exported at 2× for retina; WebP format with PNG fallback
- [ ] SVGs are minified and display correctly at all breakpoints
{% endif %}
{% if "print" in platform_targets | lower %}
- [ ] Bleed and safe margin correct per printer spec
- [ ] Color mode: CMYK (not RGB) for print files
- [ ] Resolution: ≥300 DPI for all raster elements
{% endif %}
{% if "social" in platform_targets | lower %}
- [ ] Dimensions verified for each platform (do not assume spec is still current — verify)
- [ ] Text stays within platform safe zones
{% endif %}
- [ ] All layers/groups labeled; no "Layer 1", "Rectangle copy 3" layer names

## 5. Accessibility
- [ ] Color contrast passes WCAG AA for all text
- [ ] No information conveyed by color alone
- [ ] Alt text provided for all images in delivery package notes

